By default, Links will appear as blue in all browsers
A visited link is underlined and purple

Html (HyperText Markup Language) is the code that is used to structure a webpage and its content.

The standard markup language for creating web pages.
HTML elements tell the browser how to display the content.
Hypertext means that the document contains links that allow the reader to jump to other places in the document or to another altogether.

